main event: A radio engineer reported observing a bright metallic, cigar-shaped object in the sky over Appleton, Wisconsin on July 6, 1967.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 3-5 minutes and maintained a steady position in the sky.
The witness stated that the radar-like pattern observed in the sky was identical to those obtained with radar-type signals and equipment.
The object was estimated to be about 50-75 feet in length and approximately 30 feet in width.
The report includes two black and white photographs showing an aerial structure or device with multiple components or appendages.
The report concludes that the object was possibly a radar reflection or some type of unidentified aerial phenomenon.
photographs: yes, the report includes two black and white photographs
